&lt;p&gt;What is the best way to copy text to the clipboard (multi-browser)?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have tried:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-js s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;copyToClipboard&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-params&quot;&gt;text&lt;/span&gt;) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable language_&quot;&gt;window&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-property&quot;&gt;clipboardData&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// Internet Explorer&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable language_&quot;&gt;window&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-property&quot;&gt;clipboardData&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;setData&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;Text&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, text);
    } &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
        unsafeWindow.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-property&quot;&gt;netscape&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-property&quot;&gt;security&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-property&quot;&gt;PrivilegeManager&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;enablePrivilege&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;UniversalXPConnect&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
        &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; clipboardHelper = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title class_&quot;&gt;Components&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-property&quot;&gt;classes&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;@mozilla.org/widget/clipboardhelper;1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;].&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;getService&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title class_&quot;&gt;Components&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-property&quot;&gt;interfaces&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-property&quot;&gt;nsIClipboardHelper&lt;/span&gt;);
        clipboardHelper.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;copyString&lt;/span&gt;(text);
    }
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But in Internet Explorer it gives a syntax error. In Firefox, it says &lt;em&gt;unsafeWindow is not defined&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A nice trick without using &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flash&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;Flash&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/17527870/how-does-trello-access-the-users-clipboard&quot;&gt;How does Trello access the user&apos;s clipboard?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
